    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="160"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 P 43/917: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 26, 1918—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Your 116 November 18, noon.<note n="30" xml:id="d160fn30">Not printed.</note>
                    For <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName>. Following list of members of
                    Commission excluding President’s party:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Robert Lansing</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_WH1"
                        >Henry White</persName>, Commissioners Plenipotentiary.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HL2">Leland Harrison</persName>, Assistant Secretary of
                    the American Commission to Negotiate Peace; <persName>J. K. Huddle</persName>,
                    confidential clerk to Assistant Secretary; <persName>Sydney Y. Smith</persName>,
                    drafting expert; <persName>H. E. Fenstermacher</persName>, <persName>S. Y.
                        Skinner</persName>, recording and filing clerks;</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_PPH1">Philip H. Patchin</persName>, Assistant Secretary of
                    the American Commission to Negotiate Peace; <persName>R. B. Macatee</persName>,
                    confidential clerk to Assistant Secretary; <persName>C. B. Welsh</persName>,
                        <persName>H. C. Coney</persName>, <persName>L. W. Ronimus</persName>,
                        <persName>L. E. Mundy</persName>, <persName>H. Goldstein</persName>,
                    clerks;</p>
                <p>
                    <persName>William McNeir</persName>, Disbursing Officer of the American
                    Commission to Negotiate Peace; <persName>George H. Harris</persName>, Assistant
                    Disbursing Officer.</p>
                <p>Major <persName corresp="#p_SJB1">James Brown Scott</persName>, Technical
                    Adviser; <persName>George A. Finch</persName>, Professor <persName>Amos S.
                        Hershey</persName>, <persName>Henry G. Crocker</persName>, Assistants to
                    Technical Adviser; <persName>George D. Gregory</persName>, Confidential
                    Secretary to Major <persName corresp="#p_SJB1">Scott</persName>.</p>
                <p>Specialists in charge of Expert Information, Cartography and Library: <persName
                        corresp="#p_MSE1">S. E. Mezes</persName>, Director; <persName>J.
                        Storck</persName>, Confidential clerk; <persName corresp="#p_BI1">I.
                        Bowman</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_YAA1">A. A. Young</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCH1">C. H. Haskins</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_LWE1">W. E. Lunt</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_LRH1">R. H.
                        Lord</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_WWL1">W. L. Westermann</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_SC1">C. Seymour</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_DC1"
                        >C. Day</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BGL1">G. L. Beer</persName>;
                    Assistants to Specialists: <persName>W. S. Ferguson</persName>, <persName>R. J.
                        Kerner</persName>, <persName>P. T. Moon</persName>, <persName>L. H.
                        Gray</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_DRB1">R. B. Dixon</persName>, Major
                        <persName>D. W. Johnson</persName>, Captain <persName corresp="#p_HSK1">S.
                        K. Hornbeck</persName>, Captain <persName>William C. Farabee</persName>.</p>
                <p>Cartographers and draftsmen: <persName corresp="#p_JM1">M. Jefferson</persName>,
                    Chief Cartographer; <persName>A. K. Lobeck</persName>, <persName>C. G.
                        Stratton</persName>, <persName>W. J. Blank</persName>, <persName>J. B.
                        Stubbs</persName>.</p>
                <p>Librarian, <persName corresp="#p_SJT1">J. T. Shotwell</persName>; <persName>D. P.
                        Frary</persName>, <persName>P. W. Slosson</persName>, Assistant
                    Librarians.</p>
                <p>Commissioner <persName>White</persName>’s manservant.</p>
                <p>Following ladies accompanying party: Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_LR1"
                        >Lansing</persName>, Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName>, Mrs.
                        <persName corresp="#p_MDH1">Miller</persName>, Mrs. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SJB1">Scott</persName> and Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_MSE1"
                        >Mezes</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
